title: For Sale:  Remington Magnum 870 WINGMASTER 20ga
postcontent:
This is NOT the lower quality, value priced 870 Express. OK?
This is the real deal. 
It is a top of the line 870 Wingmaster chambered in 20 gauge and it is absolutely beautiful. 
Do NOT confuse this with the Lightweight Wingmaster either. Frame is stamped Magnum. Serial number V121xxxN 
Prefix "V" designate it as manufactured between 1978 and 1984
Suffix "N" designates it as a 20 gauge Heavy Frame Magnum (remingtonsociety.com) 
28" vent rib. Barrel is marked "MOD" (presumed modified) and "20 gauge Magnum for 3" Shells".
I believe that my dear departed father rarely, maybe even never, fired this shotgun. It had sat in his gun case since the early eighties. (he liked to buy stuff, but not use it much, if at all) 
Minor light surface wear from handling. Minimal slide wear. NOTHING in the receiver. 
The slide racks like it is all floating on ball bearings.
Like new bluing. (I am not kidding) 
Knurling on takedown knob is extremely sharp and unworn.
The furniture is museum quality.

Speer's Gold Dot Hollow Point duty ammunition is the standard that all other duty ammunition is compared to. This load is tailored specifically for the law enforcement community and it is great for home defense as well! Featuring Speer's bonded core technology, this round performs great in the FBI tests.

Speer's bonded core bullets are ideally suited for barrier penetration as the jacket is bonded to the lead core of the bullet. title: For Sale/Trade:  Free Advice: HOW TO Bargain/Haggle in this gimme-gimme world
location: North Carolina, North Carolina, United States
postcontent:
Folks, this is how it works:
1. I offer goods for a price.
2. You counteroffer your lower price.
3. We find a price somewhere in between that makes us both happy. 
4. You purchase goods for the agreed upon price OR we don't come to an agreement and you walk away.

Is this a NEW concept to people here?? Questions like "what's the lowest price you will take" or "what's the least you'd take" displays laziness and is rude. Learn by the above directions and stop playing games.
Thank you.
